    Game Notes:
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
    There are five lights on the board and it&#039;s Go, Go, Go, as F1 2001
    arrives...
    With the 2001 season nearing its end and Michael Schumacher already
    crowned world champion, it&#039;s been a fairly anti-climactic conclusion to
    what would normally be a hectic finish to the Formula One calendar. 

    But what if David Coulthard had been able to mount a consistent
    challenge, or Williams had hit form earlier in the season - how
    would this season&#039;s championship have panned out then? Only one way
    to answer that question, and that&#039;s out on the virtual track with
    EA&#039;s eagerly anticipated and brand-spanking-new Formula One racer
    F1 2001. 

    F1 2001 is Electronic Arts&#039; young pretender to Geoff Crammond&#039;s
    established Formula One crown, and from all the indications we&#039;ve seen
    so far, it really does have the potential to be a real contender in the
    Formula One stakes.
